column8: The abstract, geometric, monumental design is perfectly representative of this world-renowned sculptor. “Chevron” stands a majestic 50’ tall and 30’ wide looking out at Lake Michigan at the entrance to Diversey Harbor.

Salvador’s sculpture, Camiñantes, was selected for its relevance to Chicago, and is fittingly installed in the Little Village neighborhood. The sculpture represents the journey and the resilience of both our immigrant population and all those who identify as BIPOC.a
